        "title": "How to combine functionalities of SourceWithContext and SourceQueue in Java?",
        "body": "<p>I want to create a Akka stream <code>Source<\/code> to which I'm able to push data whenever my API endpoint is called. Also, I want to pass context/metadata along with elements. I checked out <code>SourceQueue<\/code> which supports pushing elements. There is <code>SourceWithContext<\/code> which allows passing context/metadata along with elements. <code>SourceWithContext<\/code> supports operations which automatically propagate the context of an element. I want to combine these two functionalities i.e. I want push mechanism along with automatic context propagation.<\/p>\n",
